& [SOPLanguagePrimerForLocalAgents078] is the realized local-worker primer gate
  + [moment] is the failed exact-output retry suggested the LM Studio agent was receiving framework-shaped instructions before it had been introduced to SOP language
  + [focus] is language introduction before framework assignment
  + [inside] is marker set, attention delineation, outside rule, source authority, evidence gate, no-tool rule, exact-output schema, and comprehension check
  + [boundary] is local worker language readiness only; it is not framework authority, repo authority, or proof of task competence
  + [outside] is hidden model state, unprimed framework assignment, repo mutation, tool attempts, adjacent substitution, and syntax mimicry without content
  + [wisdom] is a local model should first learn the symbols and boundaries of the language before being asked to operate inside a SOP framework
  + [caution] is a worker can mimic nearby words such as SpecificationGovernance without understanding the requested SOP output shape
  + [balance] is stable because the primer separates language comprehension from framework obedience and task execution
  + [next_step] is rerun a nested Codex CLI LM Studio smoke test using a primer packet before the exact-output task

  = must: introduce SOP notation before SOP framework packets
  = must: require no-tool exact-output comprehension before worker readiness
  = should: score adjacent substitution as a primer failure

